void arrangeDataLACtrmm ( complex *restrict  ptrA,
int  kLoc,
int  mCnt,
int  kCnt,
int  flagDiagisU 
)

zero out lower part of A moved to internal memory (size MPARTITION by KPARTITION) for lower triangular A. This function also sets diagonal elements to unity if necessary. This function is used to properly properly arrange A in L2 memory for lower triangular A when C is calculated.

Parameters:
[in,out]ptrApointer to A
[in]kLoclocation of start of triangular part; zero means upper left; positive value shows offset on the upper side negative value indicate offset on the left side
[in]mCntnumber of rows in A
[in]kCntnumber of columns in A
[in]flagDiagisUflag to indicate if A is unit triangular or not
